2010/12/14

  - Mac OSX Notification Overview
  - IO#stat is equivalent to sys/stat.h#stat http://ruby-doc.org/core/classes/IO.html#M002237
    #restat is written by replacing a file's internal @stat to a re-read one.
    
    f = File.open('design.html')  # f.stat is fixed forever
    def f.restat
      @stat = File.stat(@path)  # monkey-patch and replace the internal stat
    end
    f.readlines
    f.restat
    f.readlines

