2010/10/13

  - Foo.instance_methods(true, true) to show obj-c methods

  - I think NSInputStream in a run loop is the right way to read files

  - 'select' returns an array, and app developer is responsible
    for checking whether you want to do something w/ the descriptors
    
  - adding 'r+' to File.open lets you keep 'select'ing
    t = 0
    fd = File.open('entry.rb', 'r+')
    while true
      puts t
      results = Kernel.select([fd], [], [], 15)
      if f = results.first[0]
        puts f.readlines.inspect
      else
        puts 'nothing to read'
      end
      sleep 2.5
      t += 1
    end

